---
import DemoLayout from '@/layouts/DemoLayout.astro'
---

<DemoLayout
  title="WebMCP Kit Investor Memo"
  description="Investor memo for WebMCP Kit"
  robots="noindex,nofollow"
>
  <section class="memo-shell">
    <header class="memo-hero">
      <p>Investor memo</p>
      <h1>Safe, typed app actions for browser agents.</h1>
      <span>
        WebMCP Kit is an open-source adoption wedge for making existing web apps agent-operable
        without giving agents raw browser control.
      </span>
    </header>

    <section class="memo-grid" aria-label="Investor memo sections">
      <article class="memo-lead">
        <span>Thesis</span>
        <h2>Agents need app-owned tools, not brittle UI automation.</h2>
        <p>
          Browser agents can click around, but production software needs typed actions, schema
          validation, guards, confirmation, audit trails, and app-owned execution. WebMCP Kit
          packages that contract for modern web apps.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <span>Wedge</span>
        <h2>Free SDK distribution</h2>
        <p>
          Developers adopt the kit to expose route-scoped tools from existing apps. The demo proves
          the core loop: natural language becomes a planned tool call, then the app validates and
          executes it.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <span>Monetization</span>
        <h2>Hosted planner tokens first</h2>
        <p>
          Keep the SDK free. Charge for a hosted planner API that handles provider keys, model
          routing, retries, caching, schema prompting, and usage metering.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <span>Expansion</span>
        <h2>Devtools, audit, recipes</h2>
        <p>
          Once teams register tools across routes, they need replay history, tool diffs, coverage,
          confirmation analytics, policy checks, and verified recipes for common workflows.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <span>First buyer</span>
        <h2>AI-forward SaaS teams</h2>
        <p>
          The first customer is a technical team that already wants agents inside its product but
          does not want unsafe browser automation, custom planner prompts, or unreviewable actions.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="memo-band" aria-label="Business model">
      <div>
        <span>Business model</span>
        <strong>Free SDK plus paid hosted planning</strong>
      </div>
      <dl>
        <div>
          <dt>Free</dt>
          <dd>Core kit, framework helpers, local fallback planner, demo, docs.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>Paid first</dt>
          <dd>Hosted planner token packs with usage-based pricing.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>Paid later</dt>
          <dd>Devtools Pro, enterprise audit, analytics, verified recipes.</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </section>

    <section class="memo-grid memo-grid--compact" aria-label="Execution plan">
      <article>
        <span>Now</span>
        <h2>Make the demo convert</h2>
        <p>
          Lead with four proof flows: scoped context, chained confirmation, guard blocks, and
          form-backed tools.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <span>Next</span>
        <h2>Build hosted planner MVP</h2>
        <p>
          One account token, one `/plan` endpoint, successful-plan debit, basic usage logs, and
          app-server integration docs.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <span>Validation</span>
        <h2>Find five design partners</h2>
        <p>
          Target teams already prototyping browser agents inside SaaS products. Sell the safety and
          observability layer before selling scale.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>
  </section>
</DemoLayout>

<style>
  .memo-shell {
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.5rem);
    width: min(1180px, calc(100% - 32px));
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 24px 0 80px;
  }

  .memo-hero {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.7rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(244, 240, 232, 0.14);
    padding-bottom: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.4rem);
  }

  .memo-hero p,
  .memo-hero h1,
  .memo-hero span,
  .memo-grid h2,
  .memo-grid p,
  .memo-band dl {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .memo-hero p,
  .memo-grid article > span,
  .memo-band span {
    color: #e8be53;
    font-size: 0.74rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .memo-hero h1 {
    max-width: 56rem;
    color: #f4f0e8;
    font-size: clamp(2.15rem, 5vw, 4.7rem);
    line-height: 0.98;
  }

  .memo-hero span {
    max-width: 62rem;
    color: #aeb9b3;
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.5vw, 1.18rem);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .memo-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(244, 240, 232, 0.13);
    background: rgba(244, 240, 232, 0.12);
  }

  .memo-grid article,
  .memo-band {
    display: grid;
    min-width: 0;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    align-content: start;
    background: rgba(9, 14, 13, 0.95);
    padding: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.35rem);
  }

  .memo-grid .memo-lead {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
  }

  .memo-grid h2 {
    color: #f4f0e8;
    font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.3vw, 2rem);
    line-height: 1.08;
  }

  .memo-grid p,
  .memo-band dd {
    color: #aeb9b3;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .memo-band {
    grid-template-columns: minmax(14rem, 0.28fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
    border: 1px solid rgba(244, 240, 232, 0.13);
  }

  .memo-band strong {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
    color: #f4f0e8;
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 2vw, 1.85rem);
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .memo-band dl {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.85rem;
  }

  .memo-band dt {
    color: #8fa098;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .memo-band dd {
    margin: 0.16rem 0 0;
  }

  .memo-grid--compact {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .memo-shell {
      width: min(100% - 20px, 1180px);
      padding-top: 16px;
      padding-bottom: 48px;
    }

    .memo-grid,
    .memo-grid--compact,
    .memo-band {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
